1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,020
Sungwoo, have you seen Youngji?

2
00:00:08,350 --> 00:00:11,500
Youngji? Who's Youngji?

3
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:17,380
<i> [The Witch Store]</i>

4
00:00:17,380 --> 00:00:22,340
<i> [Episode 12] 
 [Goodbye, Witch Shop]</i>

5
00:00:22,340 --> 00:00:24,220
♫ <i> Throughout the long night </i> ♫

6
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:29,500
Wow. Being late on exam day?

7
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,236
We still have one minute left.

8
00:00:31,236 --> 00:00:32,900
Hyeji, did you study?

9
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:34,556
I studied the subjects for today's exam.

10
00:00:34,556 --> 00:00:37,640
She's not here.

11
00:00:39,620 --> 00:00:41,780
What is she saying?

12
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:44,300
Eunah, is Youngji not here yet?

13
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:45,899
Youngji?

14
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:47,980
Who is Youngji?

15
00:00:47,980 --> 00:00:51,500
What? Are you teaming up to fool around with me?

16
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:54,120
The seat next to you was always empty.

17
00:00:54,120 --> 00:00:58,820
And there is no one called Youngji in our school.

18
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:00,739
What are you talking about?

19
00:01:00,740 --> 00:01:03,560
It's true. There's no one named Youngji.

20
00:01:04,980 --> 00:01:08,440
<i> What's happening?</i>

21
00:01:15,520 --> 00:01:18,600
<i> Forget it. She'll be in the shop.</i>

22
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:20,680
<i> Let's focus on the test.</i>

23
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:29,640
<i> What? Why is my hand...</i>

24
00:01:34,780 --> 00:01:37,860
<i> What? I've put the answers in the wrong place.</i>

25
00:01:37,860 --> 00:01:39,640
<i> Is it because...</i>

26
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:44,100
<i> I'm casting spells on you to protect you when something bad happens.</i>

27
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:47,140
<i> Is it because of the magic insurance contract?</i>

28
00:01:47,140 --> 00:01:48,596
<i> Youngji?</i>

29
00:01:48,596 --> 00:01:50,800
This is my first time hearing that name.

30
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:53,980
The girl who ate all the tteokbokki by herself.

31
00:01:53,980 --> 00:01:56,880
- Are you talking about yourself? 
 - It wasn't me.

32
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:58,560
Hyeji, are you oky?

33
00:01:58,560 --> 00:02:00,460
I'm okay.

34
00:02:00,460 --> 00:02:02,396
Everyone, how was the test?

35
00:02:02,420 --> 00:02:05,240
Sungwoo, have you seen Youngji?

36
00:02:10,480 --> 00:02:12,160
Youngji?

37
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:15,120
Who's Youngji?

38
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:22,260
<i> What's happening all of a sudden?</i>

39
00:02:22,260 --> 00:02:26,720
<i> Sungwoo can't remember her and I can't reach her.</i>

40
00:02:30,140 --> 00:02:32,160
Drink this.

41
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:34,300
Thank you.

42
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:37,320
- Did you submit your assignment? 
 - What?

43
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:39,939
The teacher told us to submit our assignments after the test.

44
00:02:39,940 --> 00:02:43,000
Oh, right. I forgot.

45
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,300
I'm screwed.

46
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:45,640
It's okay.

47
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:48,299
The teacher suddenly told us to submit it next week. He said he doesn't want to see it today.

48
00:02:48,299 --> 00:02:49,940
That's weird, isn't it?

49
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,940
<i> I'm sure.</i>

50
00:02:52,940 --> 00:02:55,840
<i> This is because of that contract too.</i>

51
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:59,299
Hyeji, you aren't feeling sick, are you?

52
00:02:59,299 --> 00:03:01,080
No, I'm fine.

53
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:04,060
You didn't seem well all day today.

54
00:03:05,540 --> 00:03:09,000
I don't know what's happening, but cheer up.

55
00:03:10,020 --> 00:03:13,980
<i> 🪄 Thanks to our channel manager callieseier.</i>

56
00:03:13,980 --> 00:03:18,020
<i> 🪄 Thanks to our chief-segmenter porkypine90_261.</i>

57
00:03:18,020 --> 00:03:22,010
<i>🪄 Thanks to our segmenting team: umagrojas_133, arliz, ma_xt_26 and danielley_montgomery_936.</i>

58
00:03:22,830 --> 00:03:25,080
<i>[Closed] </i>

59
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:29,020
What? The shop is closed.

60
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:36,780
She should have told me before disappearing.

61
00:03:38,260 --> 00:03:41,180
How can she disappear as soon as the part-time job is over?

62
00:03:41,860 --> 00:03:43,760
That's mean.

63
00:03:45,140 --> 00:03:47,380
Hyeji.

64
00:03:47,380 --> 00:03:50,700
Sungwoo, what brings you here?

65
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:53,460
I was on my way to my house.

66
00:03:54,540 --> 00:03:57,380
Suddenly, I just wanted to take this route.

67
00:03:57,380 --> 00:03:59,420
What are you doing here?

68
00:03:59,420 --> 00:04:02,200
Oh... I'm here for my part-time job.

69
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:04,100
What part-time job?

70
00:04:05,040 --> 00:04:07,060
It's nothing.

71
00:04:07,060 --> 00:04:08,580
Do you want to go with me?

72
00:04:08,580 --> 00:04:10,900
I thought your house was in the opposite direction.

73
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:12,360
I will walk you home.

74
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:15,030
- Okay. 
 - Let's go.

75
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:19,110
<i> 🪄 Thanks to our chief-editor cerejacult.</i>

76
00:04:19,110 --> 00:04:23,130
<i> 🪄 Thanks to our general editor taeyang30.</i>

77
00:04:23,130 --> 00:04:26,340
<i> 🪄 Thanks to our translation editor mindmuse.</i>

78
00:04:26,340 --> 00:04:29,620
Hey, what's that on your bag? It's unlike you.

79
00:04:29,620 --> 00:04:31,879
Why? Isn't it cute?

80
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:34,420
- Yeah. It's not cute. 
 - Hey.

81
00:04:34,420 --> 00:04:36,360
I like it.

82
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:39,040
- Don't laugh. 
 - What did I do?

83
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:45,659
Hold your glasses up!

84
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:48,420
Cheers!

85
00:04:48,420 --> 00:04:50,080
<i> [3 Years Later]</i>

86
00:04:52,460 --> 00:04:54,580
It's been so long since we all got together like this.

87
00:04:54,580 --> 00:04:56,040
Isn't it the first time we are together since last summer?

88
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:58,940
It's because of Sungwoo being so busy as the national team player.

89
00:04:58,940 --> 00:05:02,316
Don't blame me. You were all busy.

90
00:05:02,316 --> 00:05:05,019
Right. Don't blame Sungwoo.

91
00:05:05,020 --> 00:05:08,860
He won the gold medal in the Asian game.

92
00:05:08,860 --> 00:05:10,260
Sungwoo, congratulations.

93
00:05:10,260 --> 00:05:12,176
Wow. I can't believe I have a gold medalist as a friend.

94
00:05:12,176 --> 00:05:13,820
I brag about you every day.

95
00:05:13,820 --> 00:05:15,056
Thanks.

96
00:05:15,056 --> 00:05:18,740
I knew you were good at everything from the moment I first met you.

97
00:05:18,740 --> 00:05:21,000
So, you should pay for tonight.

98
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:23,856
Even if you didn't say anything, I planned to do that. It's on me, so everyone should eat a lot.

99
00:05:23,856 --> 00:05:25,779
Really? Let's order more beer!

100
00:05:25,780 --> 00:05:28,600
- And soju. 
 - Wait.

101
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:29,956
- Eunah. 
 - Huh?

102
00:05:29,956 --> 00:05:31,740
You said you were going to stop drinking.

103
00:05:31,740 --> 00:05:34,420
Did I? When?

104
00:05:34,420 --> 00:05:37,860
You asked me to stop you from touching the glass.

105
00:05:38,420 --> 00:05:41,560
See, I'm not touching the glass.

106
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:44,780
Why is she drinking beer like that?

107
00:05:44,780 --> 00:05:46,740
Anyway, you two have been dating for so long.

108
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:49,300
Is it six years? You've been dating since the 3rd year in middle school.

109
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:52,100
Thanks to me.

110
00:05:52,100 --> 00:05:54,459
Imagine dating a guy like him for six years.

111
00:05:54,459 --> 00:05:57,160
That tells what a good person I am.

112
00:05:57,160 --> 00:05:59,739
Speaking of that, you two have been dating for almost three years, right?

113
00:05:59,740 --> 00:06:03,296
Yes. We've been getting along. We've never even fought.

114
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:06,260
Do you really think so?

115
00:06:06,260 --> 00:06:08,199
Ah... am I wrong?

116
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:10,220
Did we... fight?

117
00:06:10,220 --> 00:06:12,736
Hey, what are you doing in front of a lonely single man?

118
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:14,360
Don't you agree, Sungwoo?

119
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:15,776
Right.

120
00:06:15,776 --> 00:06:18,256
Right. I heard you are joining the army next month.

121
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:20,180
Hey.

122
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:22,560
Let's not talk about military service now.

123
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:26,400
You know... I...

124
00:06:27,100 --> 00:06:32,496
- I'm joining the army with him. 
 - Stop following me.

125
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:35,620
You have to thank me for joining the army with you.

126
00:06:35,620 --> 00:06:38,060
You two look like a couple.

127
00:06:39,260 --> 00:06:40,299
Oh, right.

128
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:42,240
On my way here, I discovered that the shop is no longer there.

129
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:44,400
The tteokbokki shop we used to go every day after school.

130
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:46,260
Really?

131
00:06:46,260 --> 00:06:49,000
The tteokbokki there was delicious. It used to come in big portions too.

132
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,980
Big portions? We used to order more because they gave small portions.

133
00:06:51,980 --> 00:06:54,196
Right. She was the one who ordered more.

134
00:06:54,196 --> 00:06:56,940
- It wasn't me. 
 - It wasn't Hyeji.

135
00:06:56,940 --> 00:06:59,140
Right. It wasn't Hyeji.

136
00:06:59,140 --> 00:07:01,320
Then, who was it?

137
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:02,980
I don't know.

138
00:07:04,020 --> 00:07:05,980
Here, please.

139
00:07:05,980 --> 00:07:07,640
Thank you.

140
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:10,720
No time to rest. Hold your glasses up!

141
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:14,740
<i>- Drink. 
 - Cheers.</i>

142
00:07:24,580 --> 00:07:28,160
Thank you, we're full now.

143
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:31,576
Right. You should be full by now.

144
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:34,400
Go easy. They can't eat what they want starting from next month.

145
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:36,640
Do you think you will never join the army?

146
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:40,780
Hey, why do you still carry this?

147
00:07:40,780 --> 00:07:42,500
Put the medal on the bag instead.

148
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:44,340
Why? It's cute.

149
00:07:44,340 --> 00:07:47,099
It's not. It looks dirty.

150
00:07:47,099 --> 00:07:48,820
Wash it, please.

151
00:07:48,820 --> 00:07:51,080
Okay.

152
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:53,180
The taxi arrived. We'll head out first.

153
00:07:53,180 --> 00:07:55,039
We're leaving.

154
00:07:55,039 --> 00:07:56,700
I have to see you before I join the army.

155
00:07:56,700 --> 00:08:00,140
- Yuho, you should buy dinner then. Okay? 
 - Okay. Bye.

156
00:08:00,140 --> 00:08:02,180
Hyeji, please share the photos we took tonight.

157
00:08:02,180 --> 00:08:03,459
Okay. Send me a message when you arrive.

158
00:08:03,459 --> 00:08:05,156
Okay. Bye!

159
00:08:05,156 --> 00:08:08,000
Wait, I want to go with you.

160
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:10,759
- Please drop me on your way home. 
 - Go away.

161
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:12,760
Bye!

162
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,450
<i>[Making Chicken] </i>

163
00:08:14,450 --> 00:08:16,360
It's time for us to go too.

164
00:08:22,180 --> 00:08:25,616
Yuho, do you remember?

165
00:08:25,616 --> 00:08:27,980
We played judo when we were juniors.

166
00:08:27,980 --> 00:08:30,276
No, I don't remember.

167
00:08:30,276 --> 00:08:32,680
Why? You were an excellent judoka.

168
00:08:32,680 --> 00:08:35,836
Right. I was surprised by your talent.

169
00:08:35,836 --> 00:08:38,440
I've erased that memory.

170
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:40,640
Oh, Hyeji.

171
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:43,540
Didn't you have a part-time job back then?

172
00:08:43,540 --> 00:08:45,040
I don't know.

173
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:49,000
She did? What part-time job? I don't remember.

174
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:52,340
I think I went there once.

175
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:54,280
Hyeji, what's wrong?

176
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:03,979
Unni, what took you so long?

177
00:09:03,980 --> 00:09:05,116
I'm so sorry.

178
00:09:05,140 --> 00:09:08,840
The Witch Association sent me a warning, so I had no choice.

179
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:10,940
I was late because of that.

180
00:09:10,940 --> 00:09:13,220
Why? Did you wait for me?

181
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:16,600
Me? No. I didn't.

182
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:20,220
What are you talking about? You must have waited for me.

183
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:28,780
You're a little late.

184
00:09:28,780 --> 00:09:30,600
I've been waiting for you.

185
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:34,820
Did you find lots of delicious restaurants?

186
00:09:34,820 --> 00:09:39,330
Of course.

187
00:09:39,330 --> 00:09:43,890
♫ <i> I don't know where my heart will go </i> ♫

188
00:09:43,890 --> 00:09:47,850
♫ <i> Honestly, I didn't think this kind of thing </i> ♫

189
00:09:47,850 --> 00:09:52,140
♫ <i> Would happen to me </i> ♫

190
00:09:52,140 --> 00:09:53,620
♫ <i> Like the sound of a bell in my mind </i> ♫

191
00:09:53,620 --> 00:09:57,340
<i> For a while, I think there's going to be a lot of fun.</i>

192
00:09:57,340 --> 00:09:59,900
<i>[A Witch Store Run By a Real Witch]</i>

193
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:03,340
♫ <i> I can feel it coming tonight </i> ♫

194
00:10:03,340 --> 00:10:07,660
♫ <i> If you recognize me </i> ♫

195
00:10:07,660 --> 00:10:11,370
♫ <i>Cause far away so lonely night</i> ♫

196
00:10:11,370 --> 00:10:15,590
♫ <i> Would throw me at you</i> ♫

197
00:10:15,590 --> 00:10:19,990
<i> 🪄 We thank all the other language moderators! </i>

198
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:35,050
♫ <i> You knew it to from my gaze</i> ♫

199
00:10:35,050 --> 00:10:39,060
♫ <i> You would be lying if you said you didn't know it </i> ♫

200
00:10:39,060 --> 00:10:43,290
♫ <i> No need to say it </i> ♫

201
00:10:43,290 --> 00:10:47,820
♫ <i>I don't know if I want you to notice </i> ♫

202
00:10:47,820 --> 00:10:51,770
♫ <i> Honestly, I didn't know this kind of thing </i> ♫

203
00:10:51,770 --> 00:10:55,960
♫ <i> Would happen to me</i> ♫

204
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:59,280
♫ <i> More than I imagined </i> ♫

205
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:03,880
♫ <i> It's driving me crazy </i> ♫

206
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:07,320
♫ <i> I can feel it coming tonight </i> ♫

207
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:11,570
♫ <i> If you recognize me</i> ♫

208
00:11:11,570 --> 00:11:15,390
♫ <i> Cuz far away so lonely like</i> ♫

209
00:11:21,230 --> 00:11:29,560
<i> [The Witch Store]</i>
